revised_title: An Eighth Memoir on Quantics: Covariants and Syzygies of Binary Quintics
tldr: This article by A. Cayley investigates the invariants and covariants of binary quintics, focusing on the covariants of degree 6 and their syzygies. It also explores the theory of equation character determination and the Tschirnhausen transformation, with a particular emphasis on the bicorn curve and its applications.
